    <div class="chatlog__messages">
        <span class="chatlog__author-name" title="cellotherapy#3304" data-user-id="252985834402349058" style="color: rgb(26,188,156)">chloe</span>


        <span class="chatlog__timestamp">08-Jun-20 06:05 PM</span>

            <div class="chatlog__message " data-message-id="719673419947311195" id="message-719673419947311195" title="Message sent: 08-Jun-20 06:05 PM">
                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">Seven days had come and gone. Nothing came of them but bad news in various ways. The promises Izabella made to Enzan and Pen were ignored. She never returned with snacks and good conversation after the first few visits. Searchman sent a blunt email in the middle of the week regarding the matter. As long as Regal was also residing in the hospital, Izabella could not be on the same floor as him. Just scrolling past it on the elevator brought dark thoughts to her head. Calculations of what she could do to him, how much leniency the law would give her if she followed through, and if it was all even worth the jail time. She had these thoughts everyday of this grim week, and each time she would stop herself from acting on them. Her son still had a chance at life. After the act of defiance that happened yesterday, she couldn&#39;t give up on him. She had to give him every second of time that he had given her. 

But today was the last day. 
If today ended in despair, Izabella would have nothing left to keep her from killing Regal. 

&quot;Доброе утро, Лайка…&quot; Izabella murmured as she opened the glass door to Laika&#39;s room. She had grabbed a paper cup filled with tap water from the hall, and carried it over to the counter where flowers had been sent to wish health. She chattered to the body in the bed, speaking about the night before and how she spoke to her husband. Anything she could do to drown out the machines, she did it. But eventually her chore ran out, as did her kind words.</span>

                                <span class="chatlog__edited-timestamp" title="08-Jun-20 06:08 PM">(edited)</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>



            </div>
            <div class="chatlog__message " data-message-id="719673753914835066" id="message-719673753914835066" title="Message sent: 08-Jun-20 06:06 PM">
                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">.
With nothing else to keep her busy, Izabella turned to return to her daily post. She looked up from the empty cup to get a proper look at the body she&#39;d be next to on this final day. From it&#39;s feet, to it&#39;s legs, it&#39;s hands, arms, and chest... Izabella dreaded going further, but willed herself to do it. To look at it&#39;s neck, it&#39;s chin, lips, nose and-

&quot;Oh...&quot; Izabella whispered in her shock. 

The cup in her hands tumbled to the floor, barely making a sound. Emotion overtook her as she lunged to her seat. She stared in disbelief, tearing up as two dark blue eyes half stared back at her. It felt like it had been ages since she had last seen them. 

Enzan and Pen&#39;s PET would alert to a new email shortly after. The subject was blank because it was sent in such a hurry. It was from Searchman, and the body of the email only held three words. 

&quot;<em>He is awake.</em>&quot;</span>

                                <span class="chatlog__edited-timestamp" title="08-Jun-20 07:10 PM">(edited)</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>



            </div>
