    <div class="chatlog__messages">
        <span class="chatlog__author-name" title="Penelope &#128012;&#127812;Novella#4675" data-user-id="254710729934897153" style="color: rgb(255,0,0)">Anna</span>


        <span class="chatlog__timestamp">23-Jun-20 12:26 PM</span>

            <div class="chatlog__message " data-message-id="725024101424693369" id="message-725024101424693369" title="Message sent: 23-Jun-20 12:26 PM">
                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">&quot;Penelope!&quot; Role tried to keep her exclamation to a minimum. Her PET volume was maxed out for this exact reason. Though, perhaps, they were anticipating something more frightening. Pen sat down her book and stared up at Enzan&#39;s sleeping body. He&#39;d fallen asleep in a haze of grief, unable to take the mounting anticipation of the worst. 

&quot;What is it, Role?&quot; Pen said, voice thin with fear. 

Blues&#39; hologram appeared on Enzan&#39;s bedside. Suddenly, both navis were talking at once, their illuminated frames moving quickly, like pixies. It wasn&#39;t the mournfulness Pen had been expecting, no, this was a joyous sound. Pen was overwhelmed by them, but could glean one thing as Enzan stirred. 

Laika. The final day of waiting, and he wasn&#39;t dead. The navis grew quiet, and everyone in the room stared at Enzan. He sat up straight, staring at the door. His breathing was heavy. 

&quot;Get me a wheelchair,&quot; he commanded Pen. The tone of a superior officer rang from his chest.

&quot;Enzan- you shouldn&#39;t be sitting. I- I&#39;ll video call you in-&quot; 

&quot;No. Get me a wheelchair,&quot; he said again, fists clenched into the hospital sheets. All his wounds were burning from the movement, but he didn&#39;t care. 

&quot;Okay, don&#39;t get up on your own.&quot; Pen stood up. She grabbed her PET and raced out of the room. But, she didn&#39;t head for the resource station on this floor first. Instead, she raced to Laika&#39;s room. Enzan would forgive her someday, just for these brief moments. She had to know more before he made a mistake that cost him weeks of healing.</span>

                                <span class="chatlog__edited-timestamp" title="23-Jun-20 01:03 PM">(edited)</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>



            </div>
