            <div class="chatlog__message " data-message-id="725355187413188679" id="message-725355187413188679" title="Message sent: 24-Jun-20 10:22 AM">
                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">Izabella stood by the glass outside the room, watching as a medical team stood around Laika&#39;s bed. She could barely see anything with all the tears clouding her eyes. Dabbing them away was a futile effort, and keeping them back was only successful if she clenched her apron in her fists. As each assessment was taken, each test scored, she watched intently. The curtain of doctors and nurses only pulled away when they started to keep time and watch the machines. 

Laika&#39;s eyes were still open, but it looked like they had done nothing to him. Every tube and wire was still in place. Maybe there were even more now. 

Searchman appeared on Izabella&#39;s shoulder, dutifully informing her on what he could hear from inside the room. Once the update was complete, he looked down the hall to find Pen approaching. His expression remained the same as it ever was. He noted the approaching ally to Izabella, but she only nodded in response. She couldn&#39;t take her eyes off the room. 

&quot;<em>Penelope,</em>&quot; Searchman greeted once she was close enough. &quot;<em>They have asked us to wait out here until they are finished.</em>&quot; 

Izabella&#39;s lips opened, but all she managed was a strangled mess of words in her native tongue. A familiar name was twisted up in them. 

Searchman translated. &quot;<em>She is asking how Enzan took the news, and... apologizing for not coming to say it in person.</em>&quot;</span>

