Searchman allowed a pause as the doctors started speaking to each other in the room. They gave directions to a nurse, who immediately complied and walked out of the room. She didn&#39;t stop to speak with the two women at the windows, but her serious look had a tinge of hope pulling at the corner of her lips. 

&quot;<em>I have gathered that they will attempt weaning in a few hours once the proper drug has taken effect. If you can, have Enzan wait until then.</em>&quot;</span>

