                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">Penelope rubbed Izabella&#39;s back. Enzan was forgotten, just for this moment. One person at a time, one tragedy to hold on her back at once. 

&quot;It&#39;s going to be alright, now,&quot; Penelope promised on a leaden tongue. Who was she to promise that? But she needed to hear the words too. She hiccuped and cried along with her. &quot;He will be alright.&quot; Quiet hushes and soothing noises hissed from Penelope when she lost her own string of words. 

Role stood close to Searchman, with her head down. She hugged her arms around her chest to avoid touching him again. She glanced over, offering the emotions on her face instead. 

Finally, after a long moment, long after Penelope felt her back ache from leaning down to embrace her, Penelope pulled away. 

&quot;I&#39;ll keep Enzan occupied a while longer,&quot; Pen rubbed her eyes. She reached in her pocket and offered Izabella a packet of tissues.</span>

