&quot;<em>We will give you important updates.</em>&quot; Searchman stated. &quot;<em>Thank you.</em>&quot; 

&quot;Thank you.&quot; Izabella repeated. She dabbed her eyes with a tissue. The nurse that had left before walked back in, carrying a tray with a syringe and the medicine the doctor requested earlier.

While one of the doctors administered, another walked towards the glass and gestured Izabella to enter. She blinked in mild shock, then stepped away from Pen hesitantly. Another wobbly smile was given to her before she walked in. The doctor looked at her kindly, speaking just out of earshot. The rest left after their job was done, leaving the two alone in the room. 

Behind her, Laika&#39;s head shifted slightly. His eyes did a slow blink, but they were still bleary and unfocused. Izabella looked to him while Searchman translated before closing her eyes and taking a deep breath. She moved to sit down on the stool that was always there, taking up her usual position by Laika&#39;s side. The doctor continued on as she gently put her hand in his. When he was done, he bowed and left, leaving Izabella alone with her son. 

She squeezed Laika&#39;s hand a little bit, and started to talk slow. Nothing in particular, just things to give him a time and place. That he was safe, that his friends were safe too, and that no matter what, everything would be okay.</span>

