                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">.
Pen moved quickly to avoid getting in anyone&#39;s way. No one was guarding Laika&#39;s room now that he was stable. Enzan gripped the arm rests of his chair and stared intensely at the door until it opened. 

Blue met blue. Laika was alive. Enzan&#39;s heart lept out of his chest and into his mouth, holding his tongue hostage because how could this be real? Pen rolled him closer to the bedside. Enzan reached out before tears blinded him. A shaky hand took Laika&#39;s.</span>

