                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">Laika&#39;s gaze went to the glass wall that separated his room from the hallway. There were two figures just beyond what he could focus on, and he couldn&#39;t move his neck to fix that issue. The door slid opened, allowing them in. As they came closer, Laika could put them into view. Tall girl, boy with white and black hair. Very familiar, just like the woman. But... names couldn&#39;t be drawn to mind. 

The oxygen mask over Laika&#39;s nose and mouth fogged with each puff of breath his produced. Most of his gaunt features were covered by gauze and tape, hiding away the barely healing wounds underneath. A brace kept his neck in place and his hair was gone. It was the same story for the rest of him. There wasn&#39;t even a blanket to keep him covered.

Laika&#39;s eyes fluttered at the return of touch. It was different than before. The boy held his hand tight, almost painfully. Still, he found it nice. Laika found himself staring at the one holding his hand, just like he had done before. He knew these people, closely like the woman, it just wasn&#39;t clear how yet.

&quot;<em>Mr. Ijuuin, Penelope.</em>&quot; Searchman appeared on the table where Laika&#39;s PET laid. &quot;<em>It is past visiting hours. Know that I cannot guarantee any length of stay because of that.</em>&quot;</span>

