            <div class="chatlog__message " data-message-id="734938017424211999" id="message-734938017424211999" title="Message sent: 20-Jul-20 09:01 PM">
                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">&quot;I know, I-&quot; Penelope started, and Enzan finished. 

&quot;I knew the risk,&quot; Enzan said. His wide eyes remained locked to Laika&#39;s, trying so hard to remind himself of reality. This was him, right? Not the imposter. Not The Other. Sight, blue. Touch, not as warm as it should be. Hearing, beeps, beeps- tears rolled down Enzan&#39;s cheeks. Sight, touch-

&quot;Laika-&quot; he choked. Pen placed her hand to Enzan&#39;s better shoulder. &quot;Laika, Laika, Laika-&quot; his voice warbled quietly in the room. &quot;We made it. We&#39;re okay. Laika- we&#39;re alive.&quot; 

Pen changed her hold to touch Enzan&#39;s hair and offer soothing touches. He did a good job keeping his crying quiet. He lowered his head to Laika&#39;s hand, just the small part without bandages covering them. He kissed his last knuckle.</span>

                        </div>
                    </div>



            </div>
    </div>
</div>



