                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">Laika blinked slow, staring at whatever part of the boy was still in view. The name he said on repeat was his own, and hearing it brought a little more clarity. His pinky and ring finger curled in a bit at the kiss. The pulse monitor saw a slight uptick in activity. 

Searchman turned his head to check it, but said nothing. 

Not much else happened for a long moment. Laika&#39;s focused waned occasionally, his eyes coming close to shutting as he looked at different spots in the room. Pieces were coming into place at an awkward rate. He drew in a slightly deeper breath than the shallow rhythm he had been keeping, and his gaze went back to the white he could see near his hand. These were friends and... loved ones. A very specific someone. 

Laika&#39;s eyes grew a little wider, as did his mouth. Nothing came of it but more fog on the inside of his oxygen mask. Not even a strangled sound, just a puff to exchange gases from the system. He tried to move his fingers again, trying to find something to respond to Enzan.</span>

