&quot;L-laika-&quot; Enzan pushed a wobbly smile onto his face. Laika should wake up to his joy, not misery. He was alive, really, truely alive. &quot;Don&#39;t... Don&#39;t hurt yourself. I feel you, this is real. You can rest now.&quot; 

Pen rubbed Enzan&#39;s back for another moment, and very gently petted Laika&#39;s head, where there was no wound. 

&quot;I&#39;m going to watch the door. I&#39;ll keep an eye in here. Take your time,&quot; Pen said. Enzan nodded, not taking his eyes off of Laika&#39;s. He had to keep looking into his soul to hold him there. Pen left his side to go stand in the hallway.</span>

