&quot;I... See,&quot; he said. The shock of the news just barely staved off more tears. &quot;Th-thank you, Searchman.&quot; He was teetering with each new strike- he wasn&#39;t sure his body could take it. The world was shifting with unreality through his glassy eyes. 

Sight, sound, touch... A million thoughts and plans raced through his mind, all too much to vocalize yet. 

&quot;We&#39;ll help him,&quot; he promised. &quot;We&#39;ll help, Laika. We&#39;ll- we&#39;ll- take care of you. I promise. Never leaving you again. Never.&quot;</span>

