By then, a minute or so had passed since Enzan&#39;s assurances. 

Another attempt was made, just to see if it was true. Laika opened his mouth as wide as he could. Beeping from the monitors covered up the eerie silence. His eyes closed and squeezed in upset, but no tears came. His fingers curled into more against Enzan&#39;s hand. They brushed and tapped after a beat, slowly but steadily.</span>

