He leaned in, despite the pain it caused him, and kissed Laika&#39;s last knuckle again. 

He did the movement quickly- it wasn&#39;t for the newcomer. He glared up at the woman in the doorway. And Penelope. 

&quot;Penelope will take me back- to my room,&quot; he said. He clutched to the bedsheet for a moment longer. Pen peeked in through the door, as the nurse moved in to check on Laika&#39;s vitals. Enzan nodded, so she slinked in, apologized under her breathe, and moved to man his wheelchair. Enzan held in a groan of pain as he was moved. He leaned back against her arm, looking back at Laika. 

He couldn&#39;t leave him. They couldn&#39;t part again. But the wheels were already rolling out the door. He gripped the armrest of his chair. No, no, just a few more minutes- 

&quot;I love you,&quot; he called back into the room. &quot;Make sure he heard me, Pen. Make sure he knows. I love him.&quot;</span>

