                    <div class="chatlog__content">
                        <div class="markdown">
                            <span class="preserve-whitespace">Laika&#39;s eyes followed, watching Pen and Enzan until he couldn&#39;t. He had heard it, Pen didn&#39;t have to check. Not that she even could, anyways. The other nurses on the floor had come to see what the disruption was, and guided the pair to the elevator. Laika&#39;s eyes closed when he couldn&#39;t hear the muffled upset anymore. The vignette came to a close with him drifting off again. 

The nurse above him gently moved his PET back to the bedside. Then she stepped back, sticking her hands in scrub pockets and sighing. She didn&#39;t even have to dose him with anything extra. Muttering came from her as she walked out of the room, leaving Laika undisturbed. He was back to being stable, quiet, healing, and alone in the dark.

Searchman relaxed, the space now threat-less. He watched his operator like a hawk, forgoing his own rest to keep Laika secured.  As a navi, he had the luxury of simply ignoring it. He could go without if it meant that the same mistakes wouldn&#39;t be repeated again. There he sat in the night, quiet and alone in the dark.</span>

